				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img src="/files/2014/01/India-469-1-240x180.jpg" alt="Sarah with snake charmer" width="240" height="180" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-744" /><p>I have the good fortune of going to India for a month this winter. This will be my second trip (this photo is from my first trip in 2008!), this time traveling with my husband Ben.  We will spend three weeks at <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saccidananda_Ashram" target="_blank">Saccidananda Ashram</a> in Thannirpalli, which is in the very south of India.</p>
<img src="/files/2014/01/India.ashram-1-180x240.jpg" alt="The ashram" width="180" height="240" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-745" /><p>From there we will go to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arunachala" target="_blank">Mt. Arunacula</a> for a 5 day silent retreat.</p>
<p>I will be bringing my portable studio with drawing/painting supplies, embroidery materials and of course a camera! I look forward to sharing my photos and stories on all the beautiful colors, food, people,  fabrics and art!</p>
